records.addlTxt: 3:20 pm case called. Defendant Walter K. Lamacki in court with attorney Jonathan Thomas Groh.  Defendant Walter K. Lamacki in custody.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement reached-argued sentence.   Defendant advised of potential punishment.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea:  Guilty to both counts. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses the second & subsequent enhancer. Sentencing argument by DA Blader. Sentencing by Attorney Groh. Statement by defendant. Court sentences the defendant to EACH COUNT: 36 months WSP to be served as 18 month IC and 18 month ES. Concurrent to each other and Consecutive to any sentence the defendant currently serving. Credit for 10 months served. CONDITIONS of ES: AODA and follow through, Absolute Sobriety, No bars, not to possess nor ingest any controlled substances that are not prescribed by a physician. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Terms of Agent.  DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Court does not find defendant eligible for Substance Abuse Program or Challenge Incarceration Program.  Appeal Rights Given.
